description._content: Catalog #: 09_01592 Title: Elwyn H. Gibbon Special Collection Photo Agra India Additional Information: Aerial view of the Taj Mahal surrounded by scaffolding in anticipation of a German Luftwaffe or Japanese Air Force attack, Elwyn Gibbon (b.1911 d.1942) was an American pilot who served as a pilot in the Chinese Air Force in the Foreign Volunteer Squadron. Later he served as a Vultee Aircraft Company test pilot in Karachi, India, where he died in a plane crash in 1942. Tags: Elwyn H.
